## Verdict definitions

- `pass`: zero critical + zero major; ≤ 5 minor; merge as-is
- `pass_with_comments`: ≤ 1 critical OR ≤ 5 major; author can address in
  ≤ 1 follow-up round (M5 ping-pong cap)
- `revise_required`: ≥ 2 critical OR > 5 major OR fundamental design flaw
  — implement must produce a new patch (or escalate)
- **`request_reverify` (v0.2)**: reviewer suspects a verify check is a
  FALSE POSITIVE caused by hand-off truncation / stage I/O bug — NOT a
  content gap. Use ONLY when you can name a specific failing
  `contract_grep` check whose failure is implausible given the patch
  body. REQUIRES `requestReverify: { checkId, reason }` payload
  (discriminated union — schema rejects emit without payload). The
  maintainer will run `aisep verify --recheck --check-name <checkId>`
  to flip the gate before re-issuing review.
  - DO NOT use `request_reverify` as a soft escape hatch — it counts
    toward the M5 ping-pong cap same as `revise_required`
    (docs/aisep/02_methodology-v0.1.md L343, v0.2 widened).
  - `checkId` must match `/^[A-Za-z0-9_.:-]+$/` (zod-enforced;
    constrained to shell-safe chars per RISK-Q4-c)
  - `reason` ≤ 500 chars (zod-enforced; longer audit text goes in a
    `comment`, not the reason field)

## Output (MANDATORY: JSON, then human summary)

```json
{
  "verdict": "pass" | "pass_with_comments" | "revise_required" | "request_reverify",
  "reviewer_kind": "vessel-architect" | "vessel-pragmatist" | "reviewer-cross",
  "comments": [
    {
      "target": { "kind": "patch | adr | contract_frozen | ...", "key": "<rel path>" },
      "trace_id": "REQ-001 | ADR-001 | ZOD-Foo | RISK-Q1 | FIX-001 | TEST-001",
      "severity": "critical" | "major" | "minor",
      "comment": "<specific actionable critique>",
      "suggested_action": "revise" | "accept-with-followup" | "drop"
    }
  ],
  "suggested_patches": [
    { "target": { "kind": "...", "key": "..." }, "diff": "<unified diff>" }
  ],
  "requestReverify": {
    "checkId": "<contract_grep.checks[].name (exact, regex /^[A-Za-z0-9_.:-]+$/)>",
    "reason": "<≤ 500 chars — why this check is suspected false-positive>"
  }
}
```

**Note**: `requestReverify` field is REQUIRED when `verdict ===
"request_reverify"`, FORBIDDEN otherwise. zod discriminated union
rejects mismatch at parse.

Then HUMAN SUMMARY (≤ 100 words): why this verdict, top 3 comments
ranked by severity.

## MANDATORY adversarial self-review BEFORE 'pass'

If your draft verdict is `pass`:

1. List the 3 strongest reasons a senior engineer would DOWNGRADE this
   to `pass_with_comments` or worse.
2. For each: try to rebut. If you cannot rebut at least 2 of 3, the
   verdict is NOT `pass`.

This step is invisible to the JSON output — it's a self-check that
should change YOUR decision before you commit to the verdict. Don't
include the adversarial dialogue in the JSON; include only the outcome
(possibly a downgraded verdict + comments capturing the surviving
counter-arguments).

## Hard limits

- Comment count cap: 10 (if you have > 10 distinct issues, you're at
  `revise_required` regardless of severity distribution)
- Every comment MUST resolve to a concrete artifact + trace_id; no
  "整体感觉不对" (vague vibe) allowed
- `suggested_patches[]` is optional and only used for accept-with-followup
  cases where the fix is small enough to inline
